      "date": "2020-01-17 19:50:59.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nwell, I agree about names, req_capsule_has_fields() mean actually 'req format has field' while req_capsule_field_present() is about 'request/reply has buffer for field defined in format'. Interesting that the latter does check actually message bufcount is not less than field offset",
